<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Classic Explorer Skin that displays on initial/main page]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6423&amp;p=27939#p27939"><![CDATA[
I knew the annotations were just mark-ups, but I did like the actual screen design/skin that was illustrated in the sample. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />Unfortunately, this is an out-of-the-box new computer that came pre-installed with Windows 10. I suspect my only options are to run 7 virtual or dual, but will need to learn how to do that.<br /><br />We are going to go back to Windows 7 on one of our old computers, but it is really old &amp; slow. The other notebook we have came with 8.1 and we're not fond of that one, either. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><br /><br />I will keep looking to try to find existing skins similar to the mock-up on the main page, as I do like the simplicity and readability of it ... but at this point don't have the time to try to learn enough to design my own. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />Mahalo for your help!<div align="center"><span style="color:#ffffff;">Save</span></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14451">geckohale</a> — Tue Aug 02, 2016 3:18 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
